  <brief_title>The Influence of Hearing Discrete Phonemes in Mother's Voice in the Infant's Natural Environment and With Natural Melody on Developing Phonetic Categories Between 4-10 Months Old</brief_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Maaynei Hayesha Medical Center</agency>
      <agency_class>Other</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Maaynei Hayesha Medical Center</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to record voice samples of infant's mothers, process in samples
      to a phonetic musical piece, play the phonetic musical piece to 4-10 month old infants, and
      then test the infants in a conditioned head turning test in lab, and to analyze the results.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
